Implementation Paths
Path 1: Software-only holster using system RAM
This is the most practical starting point.
•	passive tier = system RAM
•	active tier = VRAM
•	scheduler manages promotion and demotion
•	no new hardware required
This proves the concept and can run on existing PCs.
Path 2: Smarter offload and staging runtime
This is still software-first, but more intentional.
•	pinned buffers
•	async copies
•	predictive prefetch
•	explicit hot/cold data handling
•	overlapping transfer with compute
This turns generic offload into a real architecture.
Path 3: Hardware-assisted passive VRAM
This is the longer-term version.
•	additional PCIe or CXL-attached memory
•	closer and faster than ordinary system RAM
•	software treats it as the preferred passive tier
This is not needed to validate the concept. It is a future optimization layer.
