Closing
Holster Memory is a practical response to one of the biggest bottlenecks in local AI: limited VRAM.
It does not attempt to erase the difference between fast and slow memory. It accepts that difference and organizes around it.
That is what makes it realistic.
The idea is simple: keep everything nearby, keep the hot path fast, and keep the GPU from stopping work.
